video9 = '[{ "index": 9, "transcripts": [ { "t": "1320", "d": "3023", "text": "Hi. Welcome back to www.engvid.com. I\'m Adam." }, { "t": "4437", "d": "3679", "text": "In today\'s lesson we\'re going to look at a bit of business writing," }, { "t": "8141", "d": "3979", "text": "and more specifically, we\'re going to look at abbreviations and acronyms." }, { "t": "12120", "d": "4950", "text": "But before I even start, I want you to understand that a lot of what you\'re going to see today" }, { "t": "17070", "d": "5256", "text": "applies in many situations outside of business, but I\'ll explain those when we get to them." }, { "t": "22591", "d": "5013", "text": "So, first of all: What\'s the difference between an abbreviation and an acronym?" }, { "t": "27753", "d": "6477", "text": "An \\"abbreviation\\" is a shortening of a word. Okay? It\'s one word that we cut out a bunch of letters and" }, { "t": "34230", "d": "7640", "text": "we make it shorter. So, for example, the abbreviation of the word \\"abbreviation\\" is \\"abbr.\\" Okay?" }, { "t": "42528", "d": "3665", "text": "\\"Acronyms\\", on the other hand, are basically initials." }, { "t": "50225", "d": "1945", "text": "Initials means the first letter" }, { "t": "52170", "d": "5619", "text": "of each word. And initials we usually use with people\'s names, like John Smith, his" }, { "t": "57789", "d": "6681", "text": "initials are JS. But when we want to take a bunch of words and we don\'t want to write" }, { "t": "64470", "d": "5320", "text": "all these words, we just want to make something short, but it has to be understood by basically" }, { "t": "69790", "d": "4135", "text": "whoever is going to read it, then we\'re going to use acronyms. Okay?" }, { "t": "73950", "d": "5180", "text": "So, let\'s start with the abbreviations, and in terms of business. Now, especially when" }, { "t": "79130", "d": "6391", "text": "we\'re writing, either a letter by hand like on paper or an email, these are very common." }, { "t": "85546", "d": "5400", "text": "\\"Attn:\\" means: Who are you writing to? So, \\"attention\\"." }, { "t": "90971", "d": "6296", "text": "Whose attention are you trying to get with this letter? \\"Re:\\" means \\"regarding\\"," }, { "t": "97292", "d": "2718", "text": "means: About what? Now, a lot of people might" }, { "t": "100010", "d": "5300", "text": "think that \\"re:\\" in an email means \\"reply\\", it doesn\'t. \\"Re:\\" in an email or a letter" }, { "t": "105310", "d": "4840", "text": "always means \\"regarding\\". What is the topic of the conversation? So, you know in the email" }, { "t": "110150", "d": "5696", "text": "bar it has \\"re:\\", what are you talking about when you reply to somebody? The topic. Okay?" }, { "t": "115871", "d": "5629", "text": "Next, when we end our letter, we should say who we are and what our position is in the" }, { "t": "121500", "d": "8084", "text": "company. So, whether you\'re the Assistant or the Director, you can write: \\"Asst.\\", \\"Dir.\\"" }, { "t": "129609", "d": "7251", "text": "or \\"Director\\", or Manager: \\"Mgr.\\" Notice that all three of them have a capital. So, it doesn\'t" }, { "t": "136860", "d": "4910", "text": "matter if you\'re using the full word or an abbreviation, you still have to capitalize" }, { "t": "141770", "d": "6320", "text": "the title of a position, or the title of the person\'s place in the company. Okay? So, if" }, { "t": "148090", "d": "3671", "text": "you\'re the Assistant Director, you write: \\"Asst. Dir.\\"" }, { "t": "151786", "d": "5004", "text": "Now, you\'re wondering why there\'s no dot here, and there is a dot there. There\'s a few ways" }, { "t": "156790", "d": "5480", "text": "to figure out which one to use, yes or no on the dot. Firstly, the more you read and" }, { "t": "162270", "d": "4433", "text": "the more you engage in this sort of writing, you will just see: What is the most common" }, { "t": "166740", "d": "6230", "text": "approach? But another way is a style guide. You can use The Chicago Manual of Style, that\'s" }, { "t": "172970", "d": "6710", "text": "the most common one for general purposes. Or if your company has its own style guide" }, { "t": "179680", "d": "5950", "text": "or a style sheet, look at it to see if they want a dot or they don\'t want the dot. It\'s" }, { "t": "185630", "d": "2720", "text": "really a personal choice of the company\'s. Okay?" }, { "t": "188350", "d": "5890", "text": "So, now, the main thing we have to consider is when we\'re writing something from the company," }, { "t": "194240", "d": "8340", "text": "we\'re writing it on company stationery. So, the company has pages with a letterhead. It" }, { "t": "202580", "d": "5610", "text": "means all the information is already at the top; the name, the logo, the address, etc." }, { "t": "208190", "d": "5629", "text": "So, all of this stuff might already be included, for example: which department, which building" }, { "t": "213819", "d": "4231", "text": "you\'re in, for example, in the address. We always like to take shortcuts, and we don\'t" }, { "t": "218050", "d": "4740", "text": "want to write everything. Write it short. \\"dept.\\" is enough. Everybody knows \\"dept.\\"" }, { "t": "222790", "d": "6169", "text": "means department. Building is building: \\"bldg.\\" because we just want to shorten everything." }, { "t": "228959", "d": "5481", "text": "The less, the better. When you end it, you\'re writing your name, and underneath: Who are" }, { "t": "234440", "d": "4140", "text": "you? Like, okay, I know your name, but who are you in terms of the company? So, you\'re" }, { "t": "238580", "d": "6757", "text": "writing your position. Now, you can see all this stuff on business cards, letterheads, etc." }, { "t": "245362", "d": "6318", "text": "So, next, let\'s look at acronyms. So, if you watched Rebecca\'s lesson on business acronyms," }, { "t": "251655", "d": "6820", "text": "you heard about Chief Executive Officer, \\"CEO\\", this is the boss of the company, he runs or" }, { "t": "258500", "d": "6410", "text": "she runs the whole company. Everybody answers to him or her. So, \\"CO\\" basically means Chief" }, { "t": "264910", "d": "5790", "text": "Officer, \\"Executive\\" means of the whole company, but then you have different departments or" }, { "t": "270700", "d": "7680", "text": "different areas of the company. \\"CFO\\", Chief Financial Officer, Chief Operating Officer," }, { "t": "278380", "d": "5340", "text": "Chief Information Officer, and then there\'s many other ones that you can use" }, { "t": "283745", "d": "7000", "text": "So, now we\'re going to look at some more acronyms. One thing to remember: Acronyms always use" }, { "t": "290770", "d": "7970", "text": "capital letters. Even if you don\'t need capitals in the extended version, the acronym will" }, { "t": "298740", "d": "8030", "text": "always be capital letters. \\"ETA\\", estimated time of arrival. So, you call a delivery person" }, { "t": "306770", "d": "5850", "text": "or you call a client and you want to inform them or you want to find out when the product" }, { "t": "312620", "d": "6267", "text": "will arrive, so you say... I call Amazon, my book hasn\'t arrived yet, and I say:" }, { "t": "318912", "d": "5991", "text": "\\"What\'s the ETA on my book?\\" And they write back: \\"Oh, it will be there sometime next week.\\"" }, { "t": "325060", "d": "5870", "text": "Or I need to contact somebody and get some things done, and I call the local place, and" }, { "t": "330930", "d": "5930", "text": "they say: \\"Oh, sorry, we can\'t help you. You have to call HQ.\\" Headquarters, the main office." }, { "t": "336860", "d": "6735", "text": "It will probably be capitalized even in the extension, but not the \\"q\\", notice, because it\'s one word." }, { "t": "343960", "d": "6660", "text": "\\"MSRP\\". So, now, when we\'re talking about big ticket items, like cars, computers, appliances," }, { "t": "350620", "d": "6700", "text": "then we want to know how much it costs. So, what you are paying the store might not necessarily" }, { "t": "357320", "d": "5294", "text": "be the MSRP, because the stores want to make it more competitive." }, { "t": "362639", "d": "4984", "text": "The MSRP is the manufacturer\'s suggested retail price." }, { "t": "367717", "d": "4253", "text": "So, the company that made the product tells the stores and tells" }, { "t": "371970", "d": "4770", "text": "the distributors: \\"Oh, you should sell this for $100.\\" Okay? That\'s what it\'s... That\'s" }, { "t": "376740", "d": "5790", "text": "what you can get for it. But then the stores, they want to compete with other stores, so" }, { "t": "382530", "d": "8790", "text": "they go: \\"We will beat the MSRP by 10%. We will go under the manufacturer\'s price.\\" Okay?" }, { "t": "391320", "d": "5490", "text": "\\"POS\\", point of sale. So then you go into a store, you find the product you like, you" }, { "t": "396810", "d": "4290", "text": "want to go pay for it. The cash register, the machine where you actually pay or put" }, { "t": "401100", "d": "6849", "text": "your card, or whatever, that\'s called the POS, the point of sale. Okay? \\"SOP\\", so now" }, { "t": "407949", "d": "4291", "text": "you\'ve bought your product, you take it home, and you try to use it and realize:" }, { "t": "412265", "d": "4365", "text": "\\"You know what? This is not really good. This is not what I paid for.\\" So you call the company," }, { "t": "416630", "d": "4420", "text": "you say: \\"I want to return this. Can I just take it back to the store?\\" And the person" }, { "t": "421050", "d": "4940", "text": "on the phone says: \\"No, I\'m sorry, sir, that\'s not our SOP. You have to do it this steps." }, { "t": "425990", "d": "7830", "text": "You have to go A, B, C, and then get back to HQ.\\" \\"SOP\\", standard operating procedure." }, { "t": "433820", "d": "5620", "text": "Basically: How do we do this? How is it done? How is the...? What is the policy?" }, { "t": "439440", "d": "7319", "text": "Now, you\'re working at the store and you get your paycheque, and on your paycheque it shows" }, { "t": "446759", "d": "5360", "text": "how much this cheque is for, what is your pay for this term, maybe two weeks, one month," }, { "t": "452144", "d": "7676", "text": "etc. And next to it, it will say \\"yeartodate\\". How much have you received so far from the" }, { "t": "459820", "d": "7349", "text": "beginning of the fiscal year until now? \\"Yeartodate\\". But notice that we have the hyphens, so technically," }, { "t": "467169", "d": "4981", "text": "this is like one word, but we still have an acronym for it. Yeartodate. Then you take" }, { "t": "472150", "d": "5991", "text": "all your financial information, and you go talk to your CPA about doing your taxes, for" }, { "t": "478166", "d": "6033", "text": "example. Your Chartered Public Accountant. This is an accountant who is recognized by" }, { "t": "484199", "d": "6141", "text": "the government, he... He or she has a license, and they can sign off and do your taxes, personal" }, { "t": "490340", "d": "1582", "text": "or corporate, etc." }, { "t": "492281", "d": "5108", "text": "Now, the thing to remember is that a lot of this stuff is not only used in business. People" }, { "t": "497389", "d": "5090", "text": "use ETA all the time. So, especially when we\'re texting because, you know, texting uses" }, { "t": "502479", "d": "4641", "text": "a lot of acronyms, a lot of abbreviations because people don\'t like to type too much." }, { "t": "507120", "d": "5370", "text": "So I\'m typing my friend, he\'s supposed to come over for... To hang out tonight, and" }, { "t": "512490", "d": "4518", "text": "he didn\'t come, he hasn\'t come yet. So I say: \\"Hey. What\'s your ETA?\\" I don\'t write:" }, { "t": "517033", "d": "3837", "text": "\\"When do you think you will show up?\\" I say: \\"What\'s your ETA?\\"" }, { "t": "520895", "d": "2014", "text": "And he understands estimated time" }, { "t": "522909", "d": "5170", "text": "of arrival: When are you coming? When will you be here? Okay? \\"SOP\\" is another one we" }, { "t": "528079", "d": "6670", "text": "use in many situations. The \\"SOP\\" means how something is done. And again, all of these" }, { "t": "534749", "d": "6130", "text": "are used for addresses, for business situations, for non-business situations, etc. So it\'s" }, { "t": "540879", "d": "5760", "text": "important to learn these. And again, the more you actually get involved in writing and reading" }, { "t": "546639", "d": "4870", "text": "business situations or other situations, you will see these all the time and eventually" }, { "t": "551509", "d": "3450", "text": "you will remember how to use them. Okay?" }, { "t": "554959", "d": "2349", "text": "So, I hope this was pretty clear." }, { "t": "557333", "d": "3509", "text": "If you enjoyed this lesson, please subscribe to my YouTube channel." }, { "t": "560943", "d": "5547", "text": "If you have any questions about this lesson, go to www.engvid.com, join the forum," }, { "t": "566490", "d": "4930", "text": "ask your questions-I will be happy to reply to them-and take the quiz." }, { "t": "571445", "d": "5624", "text": "There\'s also going to be a quiz to test your understanding and knowledge of these words. And, of course," }, { "t": "577069", "d": "4210", "text": "come back again soon and watch more helpful videos, and I\'ll see you then." }, { "t": "581304", "d": "713", "text": "Bye." } ] }]';